"{\"uid\": \"flotrack.org-articles-12759794-when-are-the-100m-finals-at-the-2024-olympics-what-to-know\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Adidas Indoor Nationals  Redlands Invitational  Chandler Rotary Invite  Texas Distance Festival  Run Rome the Marathon  David Noble Relays  Emory Thrills in the Hills  WashU Distance Carnival  Jim Taylor Duals  Doc Jopson Invitational  2026 FSU Relays  Continental Tour: Maurie Plant Meet  WashU Invite  Monmouth Home Opener  The 100- and 200-meter events in track and field long have been key factors in determining the fastest man and woman on Earth.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 120, \"end\": 131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_F._Noble\", \"score\": 0.9999997771715492, \"rank\": 1.463277814537909e-07, \"text\": \"David Noble\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_F._Noble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_F._Noble\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Throughout history, those titles have changed hands many times, and often on the grandest stages.\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It could happen again Saturday and Sunday in the 100-meter finals at the2024 Olympic Gamesin Paris.\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 645, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995829967, \"rank\": 4.1711746735721073e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the track and field action at Stade de France in full swing, it's time for the sprinters to claim their moments in the spotlight, no matter how brief.\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 808, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Actually, the shorter the better.\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 842, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The preliminary round of the women's 100m was completed Friday, and the 27-athlete field now is set for the semifinals, which will take place Saturday at 1:50 p.m. Eastern.\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 1016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eight women then will advance to the final, scheduled for Saturday at 3:20 p.m. EDT.\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men will hit the track at Stade de France for their preliminary heats Saturday at 4:35 a.m. Eastern and 5:45 a.m. EDT.\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1134, \"end\": 1149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The semifinals will be Sunday at 2 p.m. EDT, and the final will follow at 3:55 p.m.  As expected, reigning world championSha'Carri Richardson of the United States has advancedand will continue her quest for her first Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1358, \"end\": 1368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999976652534285, \"rank\": 2.334746400266285e-06, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 1376, \"end\": 1389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999819245650716, \"rank\": 1.565030855403007e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was fourth in the opening round with a time of 10.94.\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1516, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marie Josee Ta Lou of the Ivory Coast ran the fastest time of the day (10.87).\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1544, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9842317134127766, \"rank\": 0.010373492078538297, \"text\": \"Ivory Coast\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richardson entered the event as the favorite, and the path seemed to get a little bit easier earlier in the week when Jamaica's Shericka Jackson withdrew from the event to focus on the 200 meters.\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1598, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999976652534285, \"rank\": 2.334746400266285e-06, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.0843656915914755e-15, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1726, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shericka Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA's Melissa Jefferson (10.96) and Twanisha Terry (11.15) also qualified for the semifinals.\", \"from\": 1796, \"to\": 1894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1796, \"end\": 1804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9198532650896343, \"rank\": 0.08712990139001964, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1807, \"end\": 1824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Melissa Jefferson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\"}, {\"begin\": 1837, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twanisha_Terry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Twanisha Terry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twanisha_Terry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twanisha_Terry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In recent years at the Olympics, the event has been dominated by the Jamaicans.Shelly-Ann Fraser-Prycewon in 2008 and 2012, while Elaine Thompson won in 2016 and 2020.\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 2063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2026, \"end\": 2041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elaine Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce was tied for second place in qualifying Friday with a 10.92 performance, maintaining the expectation for a USA-Jamaica battle for the gold medal.\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See the results of the women's 100-meter prelims and the rest of the track and field action on Aug. 2.\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the men's side,Team USA's Noah Lylesmay be better-known for his prowess at 200 meters, but he's targeting a 100, 200 and 4x100 triple in Paris.\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9198532650896343, \"rank\": 0.08712990139001964, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2469, \"end\": 2474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995829967, \"rank\": 4.1711746735721073e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time an athlete from the United States won the men's 100-meter race at the Olympics was 2004 (Justin Gatlin) - then came a dominant run by Jamaica's Usain Bolt, who won it three consecutive times (2008, 2012, 2016) and is the only athlete in history to achieve that feat.\", \"from\": 2477, \"to\": 2757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2511, \"end\": 2524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999819245650716, \"rank\": 1.565030855403007e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2580, \"end\": 2593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Gatlin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Justin Gatlin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Gatlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Gatlin\"}, {\"begin\": 2625, \"end\": 2632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.0843656915914755e-15, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 2635, \"end\": 2645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Usain Bolt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles made his intentions known with a statement performance in the 100 at the recent London Athletics Meet (Diamond League London), where he ran a personal-best time of 9.81 seconds.\", \"from\": 2759, \"to\": 2942, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2845, \"end\": 2851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999993664552864, \"rank\": 5.900379998856904e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2868, \"end\": 2882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999999045031, \"rank\": 9.544494148581541e-11, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}, {\"begin\": 2883, \"end\": 2889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999993664552864, \"rank\": 5.900379998856904e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Likely, Lyles' main competition in the 100 at the Olympics will be Jamaica's Kishane Thompson, who owns the year's fastest time at 9.77.\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 3080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2952, \"end\": 2957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999733906045248, \"rank\": 2.658785952634683e-05, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 3011, \"end\": 3018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.0843656915914755e-15, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 3029, \"end\": 3037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9615526318722115, \"rank\": 0.03998467358678444, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Defending champion Marcell Jacobs of Italy also will be in the field.\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3101, \"end\": 3115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marcell Jacobs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\"}, {\"begin\": 3119, \"end\": 3124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.6529924879966865, \"rank\": 0.5294799196080123, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Times Eastern  Aug 3  Aug. 4  The Olympics are on the NBC family of networks, including the Peacock streaming app.\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"FloTrack is on the ground in Paris with the latest news.\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3302, \"end\": 3307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995829967, \"rank\": 4.1711746735721073e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the latest news and notes and vibes from Paris on FloTrack.\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3375, \"end\": 3380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995829967, \"rank\": 4.1711746735721073e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss all the track and field season action streaming on FloTrack.Check out the FloTrack schedule for more events.\", \"from\": 3395, \"to\": 3515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Video footage from each event will be archived and stored in a video library for FloTrack subscribers to watch for the duration of their subscriptions.\", \"from\": 3517, \"to\": 3668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:  Get the most important Track & Field stories delivered straight to your inbox.\", \"from\": 3670, \"to\": 3755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3700, \"end\": 3713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3200414973521339e-61, \"text\": \"Track & Field\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92006 - Present FloSports, Inc. All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3809, \"entities\": []}]}"